COPS in Mthatha in the Eastern Cape are investigating an attempted ATM bombing that took place at Myezo on Monday morning. According to cops the incident took place around 01h50. "At this stage it is not yet clear how many
perpetrators committed the crime. No money was taken, but the ATM was
damaged," the cops said. It's reported that theLocal Criminal Record Centre (LCRC) and
the Explosives Division were called to the scene and it was thoroughly examined. The cops said no arrest have been made yet. Members of the community were urged that anyone with information
that may help in identifying the suspects to contact Captain Xolile Mdepa on
0823198754 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.